column5: Well the ice was slippery today but still holding in there ..there was a good 5 " still when i walked in tonight from fishing ..walked back in with these boys that had a good night fishing ...there calling for -10 late tonight so things should still be good to go tommrow ..most groups of guys did very well tonight Buck Shots were the hot bait tipped with a couple minnows ..
Looks like I may have to give Steve's Minnows a try  tomorrow morning.
Wow nice tasty Walleye.Sounds like the bite was on.How much did the fat one weigh?
Couple nights of -10 before the snow coming on Friday would certainly help things.   May see you in the morning as well Steve  Cheers  Craig
how far is that from Barrie ?
Nice walleyes..well done guys !!!!!...well it looks like the weather hasnt stopped the walleyes from hitting....cheers
4.8lbs there was a 10.5 and 1 over 11lbs caught on the weekend ..
Takes me 2 1/2 hours to drive to Orilla from Dunnville
